I-I think…

57
00:05:01,050 --> 00:05:04,540
Did yesterday's news on TV affect you?

58
00:05:07,960 --> 00:05:13,360
Every accident on the race track can potentially lead to catastrophic consequences.

59
00:05:13,360 --> 00:05:16,499
Even the slightest loss of control is the same.

60
00:05:21,680 --> 00:05:23,220
No.

61
00:05:30,680 --> 00:05:32,680
I'll be fine

62
00:05:34,199 --> 00:05:37,020
because I trust you, and you trust me, don't you?

63
00:05:40,116 --> 00:05:44,660
As long as you are with me, the probability of me losing control is almost zero.

64
00:05:49,360 --> 00:05:51,780
But I'm still worried about you.

65
00:05:51,780 --> 00:05:56,180
It has nothing to do with physics, mathematics, or probability.

66
00:05:57,240 --> 00:06:00,839
A person's fear is not only due to the unknown,

67
